==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: emotionless
<hw>e*mo"tion*less</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>unsusceptible
to, destitute of, or showing no emotion; unmoved by feeling. Opposite of
<ant>emotional</ant>; <as>as, he kept his <ex>emotionless</ex>
objectivity and faith in the cause he served</as>.</def> [Narrower
terms: <stype>matter-of-fact, prosaic</stype>; <stype>philosophical,
philosophic</stype>; <stype>phlegmatic, phlegmatical, stolid</stype>;
<stype>stoic, stoical</stype>; <stype>unblinking</stype>] <see>Also See:
<er>cool</er>, <er>passionless</er>, <er>unmoved</er>(predicate),
<er>unmoving</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> unemotional, passionless.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emotive</ent>⟦br⟧
